abstract: The caucuses were supposed to be less important this time. But they still might pick the winner.
snippet: The caucuses were supposed to be less important this time. But they still might pick the winner.
lead_paragraph: With Cory Booker’s exit, the Democratic field has lost another minority candidate, and revived the arguments — pressed by Julián Castro before his own exit from the race — that the whiteness of the Iowa electorate explains the increasing whiteness of the Democratic field.

snippet: Her nomination would offer the best hope of bringing together the party’s warring factions.
lead_paragraph: Over the weekend, a minor conflict broke out between the presidential campaigns of Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren, longtime friends who have, until now, seemed to operate under an unspoken nonaggression pact.

abstract: How both sides are choosing the people who will make their case before the Senate.
snippet: How both sides are choosing the people who will make their case before the Senate.
lead_paragraph: In the coming days, Ms. Pelosi is expected to choose a half dozen or so managers to argue on the Senate floor for President Trump’s removal from office. Those managers, who will be selected at least partly from the House Judiciary and Intelligence committees, form just one element of a trial full of complicated procedures.

abstract: We don’t care about Biden’s electability. We want excitement.
snippet: We don’t care about Biden’s electability. We want excitement.
lead_paragraph: KNOXVILLE, Iowa — Welcome to the final Democratic debate before the Iowa caucuses. As a reporter for a small-town Iowa radio station, I have the best seat in the house for the caucuses. I’ve seen all the candidates who have come to Iowa, most multiple times, interviewed nearly all of them, some more than once, and attended countless events. The largest, the Polk County Steak Fry in September, had over 12,000 attendees. The smallest was, um, about 10 people about a week or two ago (sorry, Marianne Williamson!).

abstract: The timing and scale of the attacks suggest the Russians may be looking for the same kind of damaging information on Joe Biden that President Trump wanted from Ukraine, security experts say.
snippet: The timing and scale of the attacks suggest the Russians may be looking for the same kind of damaging information on Joe Biden that President Trump wanted from Ukraine, security experts say.
lead_paragraph: With President Trump facing an impeachment trial over his efforts to pressure Ukraine to investigate former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and his son Hunter Biden, Russian military hackers have been boring into the Ukrainian gas company at the center of the affair, according to security experts.

abstract: Ranking first is still the best, of course. But in the Iowa caucuses, second-choice candidates can win.
snippet: Ranking first is still the best, of course. But in the Iowa caucuses, second-choice candidates can win.
lead_paragraph: The snow was starting to come down. Senator Amy Klobuchar was snapping selfies at a campaign event. And Monica Peitz and Peg Raney, two friends from central Iowa, were discussing the question that it seemed every Democrat in the state was asking: Who is on your list?
